│                                                                          │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                              │
│                                                                          │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                          │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                              │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion failure in                          │
│ BoUpSLP::ScheduleData::incrementUnscheduledDeps():                       │
│ "hasValidDependencies() && 'increment of unscheduled deps would be       │
│ meaningless'". This indicates that we are attempting to increment or     │
│ decrement the unscheduled dependency counter on a ScheduleData whose     │
│ dependencies have not been initialized (Dependencies == InvalidDeps).    │
│ Assertions in LLVM are designed to catch earlier logic errors;           │
│ therefore, we must ensure we never call incrementUnscheduledDeps unless  │
│ hasValidDependencies() is true.                                          │
│                                                                          │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                  │
│ The debug log shows the SLP scheduler processing bundles and             │
│ decrementing dependencies for both def-use, memory, and control          │
│ dependencies. The crash occurs during handling of control/memory         │
│ dependencies:                                                            │
│ - "check for readiness (mem): %call"                                     │
│ - "check for readiness (ctrl): %call"                                    │
│ Right after that, the assertion fires in incrementUnscheduledDeps. In    │
│ the scheduler, DecrUnsched() is used to decrement unscheduled deps for   │
│ various dependency types, and it currently allows decrementing for       │
│ control dependencies even when hasValidDependencies() is false.          │
│                                                                          │
│ Specifically, DecrUnsched contains:                                      │
│   if ((IsControl || Data->hasValidDependencies()) &&                     │
│       Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) == 0) { ... }                   │
│ This means when IsControl is true, incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) is       │
│ invoked even if hasValidDependencies() is false, which directly violates │
│ the assertion inside incrementUnscheduledDeps.                           │
│                                                                          │
│ The logs before the crash also show several "reset schedule because ...  │
│ was already scheduled" and complex rescheduling of bundles, with         │
│ copyable elements and reused scalars. However, the immediate cause is    │
│ the unconditional decrement for control deps.                            │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ The scheduler attempts to treat control dependencies specially by        │
│ decrementing their counters even if dependency info hasn’t been          │
│ initialized (hasValidDependencies() == false). But                       │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps asserts that hasValidDependencies() must be     │
│ true. The mismatch between the DecrUnsched guard and the assertion is    │
│ the direct cause of the crash.                                           │
│                                                                          │
│ In normal flow, dependencies are initialized via calculateDependencies() │
│ before scheduling. However, control dependencies may point to            │
│ ScheduleData entities whose direct deps were cleared                     │
│ (clearDirectDependencies()), leaving Dependencies/UnscheduledDeps ==     │
│ InvalidDeps. Calling incrementUnscheduledDeps() on such data is invalid. │
│                                                                          │
│ Therefore, the root bug is the condition in DecrUnsched allowing         │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps on control deps without verifying               │
│ hasValidDependencies().                                                  │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                               │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                  │
│ - Location: In BlockScheduling::schedule(), inside DecrUnsched lambda    │
│ near lines ~5410.                                                        │
│ - Change the condition to only call incrementUnscheduledDeps when        │
│ hasValidDependencies() is true, regardless of IsControl. This aligns     │
│ with the assertion contract and prevents attempts to modify counters in  │
│ an uninitialized state.                                                  │
│                                                                          │
│ Edit:                                                                    │
│ Lines 5410-5416:                                                         │
│ From:                                                                    │
│   if ((IsControl || Data->hasValidDependencies()) &&                     │
│       Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) == 0) {                         │
│     ...                                                                  │
│   }                                                                      │
│ To:                                                                      │
│   if (Data->hasValidDependencies() &&                                    │
│       Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) == 0) {                         │
│     ...                                                                  │
│   }                                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ This prevents calling incrementUnscheduledDeps on control dependencies   │
│ unless their dependency info is valid. If dependencies are not yet       │
│ valid, we skip decrementing here; they will be processed when deps are   │
│ computed/validated.                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ By tightening the guard in DecrUnsched to require                        │
│ hasValidDependencies(), we avoid violating the invariant enforced by     │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps. This fixes the immediate crash without         │
│ altering broader scheduling semantics. Control dependencies will be      │
│ handled once their dependency data is available, preserving correctness  │
│ and stability of the scheduler.                                          │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                          │
